# Styling Guidelines

## Interactive Elements
- Use `cursor-pointer` for clickable elements
- Hover states: `hover:text-gray-900`, `hover:bg-gray-50`
- Focus states for accessibility

## Typography
- Use semantic heading hierarchy: `h1`, `h2`, `h3`
- Consistent font sizes: `text-xl`, `text-2xl`, `text-3xl`
- Proper line heights: `leading-relaxed`, `leading-tight`

## Spacing
- Use consistent spacing: `space-y-4`, `space-y-6`, `space-y-8`
- Padding: `p-4`, `p-6`, `p-8`
- Margins: `mb-4`, `mb-6`, `mb-8`

## Responsive Design
- Mobile-first approach
- Breakpoints: `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`
- Test on all screen sizes
- Use `flex` and `grid` for layouts

## Component Styling
- Use Tailwind utility classes
- Avoid custom CSS when possible
- Keep styles close to components
- Use CSS variables for theming